@stym06 : Did you try querying via spark datasource? Do you see the same. would help if we can rule out if there is any issue w/ underlying storage or some query eng specifics in play.
Also, can you post the contents of .hoodie. Wanna check if the two commits times are two writes or one is from compaction. 
@bvaradar @bhasudha @satishkotha : have you folks encountered duplicates records anytime. Any idea on why this could happen.

@Frogglet : Can you respond to my above question. 
Also, can you tell us whats the resultant column's schema in hudi after insert and after upsert? Can you try reading as parquet and let us know whats the data type. guess in hive its bigint. 

Also, can you give us the configs you set for writing. especially interested in the key generator configs. I will try to reproduce on my end.

> This is happening also in 'Delete archive instants'
> 
@h7kanna This could be due to FS timeout.  The writer may still proceed with retries after the exception.  Do you see this failing the write actions constantly?
